secureboot-watchdog (0.3) noble; urgency=medium

  * check_mok_enrollment: fix false-positive MOK_NOT_ENROLLED. The check
    was computing the SHA-256 fingerprint of each MOK .der and searching
    for it in the `mokutil --list-enrolled` output, but mokutil on noble
    only prints SHA-1 fingerprints — so the check always failed. Now
    compute both SHA-1 and SHA-256 and match either.

 -- Gitii <Gitii@users.noreply.github.com>  Wed, 17 Jun 2026 10:30:00 +0000

secureboot-watchdog (0.2) noble; urgency=medium

  * secureboot-monitor.service: set RuntimeDirectoryPreserve=yes so
    /run/secureboot-monitor/status.json survives the oneshot's exit.
    Previously the directory was wiped as soon as the service finished,
    leaving the user notifier nothing to read.

